title: Thursday’s other High School results
text:
Published: Fri, October 16, 2015 @ 12:00 a.m. 
VOLLEYBALL 
Canfield 25-25-25 Austintown Fitch 13-13-23 
AUSTINTOWN 
For Canfield, Maddy Johns had 11 kills and five blocks, Emma Hartshorn had 25 assists, and Jessica Misner had 25 digs. For Fitch, Sarah Obradovish had 15 kills and 17 digs, Bree Hunter had 9 assists, Cami Hefner had six points and three aces, and Rachael Difrancesco had four blocks. JV: Fitch 2, Canfield 1. 
LaBrae 25-25-25 Campbell 11-7-7 
CAMPBELL 
For LaBrae (14-7, 6-4), Morgan Meyer had 24 points and eight aces, Allie Middleton had 25 assists, Miranda Dodrill had 13 kills, Danielle Douce had four blocks, and Haylie Kiser had 25 digs. 
Hubbard 25-28-16-25 Lakeside 18-26-25-16 
HUBBARD 
For Hubbard, Adria Powell had 13 kills and four aces, Emily Krinos had 27 assists, and Addy Jarvis had 10 kills and 16 points. 
Heartland 25-25-25 JFK 15-16-10 
WARREN 
For Heartland (12-10), Bonnie Flynn had 22 kills and 19 digs, Jacquelyn had 14 points and two blocks, Alanna Holden had six aces, and Brianna LaRocca had 36 assists. JV: Heartland 2, JFK 0. 
Southeast 25-25-25 Cardinal Mooney 22-23-15 
YOUNGSTOWN 
For Southeast (20-1), Savannah Woodard had 38 assists, Danielle Nurquest had 11 kills, 25 digs, and two blocks. For mooney (17-5), Autumn DeSantis had eight kills and six blocks, Marcella Adams had 23 digs, and Maria Pelini had 23 assists. JV: Mooney 2, Southeast 1. 
Newton Falls 25-25-25 Champion 5-15-10 
NEWTON FALLS 
Summer Fassnacht had five digs, four assists, and one block for Champion. In addition, Ashley Naylor had 12 digs and one ace, and Morgan Tenney had eight digs for Champion. For Newton (22-0), Gabby Kline had 16 kills and 12 points, Kate Wainwright had 30 assists, Natalie Georgalas had nine digs and 11 points. 
Boardman 25-25-25, Girard 9-14-22 
GIRARD 
Makayla Trebella had seven kills, eight digs, and one ace, Megan Payich had nine digs and six service points, and Sydney Teter had two blocks for Girard. For the Spartans, Hayley Eicher had nine kills and one block, Katie Platt had 30 assists, seven digs, four kills, and three aces, and Krista Johnson had eight kills and eight digs. JV: Boardman 2-0. 
South Range 25-25-25, Springfield 21-23-23 
CANFIELD 
Lindsay Druschell had 25 assists, five points, and one ace for Springfield. Brooke Bullen contributed 12 points and one ace, and Caitlyn Cyrus also contributed seven kills and five blocks for Springfield. For South Range, Lynnie Ritter had 10 kills, one dig, two aces, and two points, Emily Moretti had seven kills, eight digs, two aces, and nine points, and Eliza Garlough had 12 digs, one ace, and 14 points. JV: Springfield 2-0. 
Jackson-Milton 25-25-25, Sebring 12-7-10 
NORTH JACKSON 
Sydney Smith had four points, one ace, and three kills, Murphy Flowers had three kills and eight digs, and Lisa Cathey had seven assists for Sebring. For the Bluejays, Kailtyn Totani had 20 points and five aces, Julissa Tomaino had 14 points, four aces, and 15 assists, and Sierra Huff had 15 kills. JV: Jackson-Milton 2-0. 
BOYS SOCCER 
Poland 6, LaBrae 0 
LABRAE 
Goals for Poland were scored by Joe Shields (2), Matthew Holsinger, Marcus Trevis, Jake Buccieri, and Reed McCreery. Trevis and Holsinger also had assists for the Bulldogs. Their goalkeeper, Bryan Montgomery, had five saves. LaBrae’s goalkeeper, Brandon Lomax, had four saves on the night. 
Hubbard 6, Campbell 0 
CAMPBELL 
Ben Rubinic, Aiden Sexton, Khaled Kassem, Bashar Rasoul, Saki Atsas, and Alex Sinopoli all scored once for Hubbard (6-5-3). Aone with Kassem, Nikolas Dowell and Mike Van Such contributed assists. Both Jake Shaffer and Dominic Weser played in the net for Hubbard, with three and two saves respectively. For Campbell, Tristan Kendall had 11 saves. 
GIRLS SOCCER 
Cardinal Mooney 3, Boardman 2 
STRUTHERS 
Carol Kay led the Cardinals with two goals, and Lexy Herman tacked on one more goal. For the Spartans, Sara Downie and Cara Higgins each had one goal. 
Canfield 3, Mentor Lake Catholic 0 
CANFIELD 
For the Lady Cardinals, Anita Mancini scored two goals off of assists by Cheyenne Story. Alana Petracci also scored a goal with an assist from Haylee Klacik for the Cardinals. Goalkeeper Olivia VanDevender had seven saves. Mentor’s goalkeeper had four saves. 
Columbiana 6, Valley Christian 2 
YOUNGSTOWN
